01:53.440 --> 01:54.590
To legends.

01:55.040 --> 01:58.192
<i>I made a name for myself</i>
<i>by doing a lot of crazy shit.</i>

01:58.280 --> 02:00.317
<i>Not all of it's true, but this part is.</i>

02:00.400 --> 02:04.280
<i>In this corner, the former</i>
<i>New Jersey heavyweight champion,</i>

02:04.360 --> 02:07.910
<i>the man who went 15 rounds</i>
<i>with Muhammad Ali, okay?</i>

02:08.000 --> 02:10.560
<i>The pride of Bayonne, Chuck Wepner!</i>

02:16.120 --> 02:17.634
<i>And in this corner,</i>

02:17.720 --> 02:20.554
<i>you know him from his</i>
<i>Hollywood movie,</i> Paint Your Wagon,

02:20.640 --> 02:22.597
<i>his many</i> Tonight Show <i>appearances,</i>

02:22.680 --> 02:26.469
<i>he's undefeated in 1,303 bouts.</i>

02:26.560 --> 02:27.710
<i>It's Victor!</i>

02:29.400 --> 02:31.756
- All right, nothing to the face, okay?
- Did you tell him that?

02:31.880 --> 02:32.916
No face.

02:38.600 --> 02:39.670
Let's go!

02:41.080 --> 02:43.436
<i>For me, it was always about</i>
<i>putting on a show.</i>

02:43.520 --> 02:46.433
<i>Even when I was a kid, growing up in Bayonne,</i>

02:46.560 --> 02:49.120
<i>me and my brother Don</i>
<i>were a couple of real clowns.</i>

02:49.200 --> 02:52.477
<i>I was not really a fighter,</i>
<i>but this was Bayonne.</i>

02:52.560 --> 02:54.995
<i>One way or another,</i>
<i>you were gonna end up fighting.</i>

02:57.320 --> 03:01.030
<i>In 1954, Malphy Esposito stole my basketball.</i>

03:02.600 --> 03:05.991
<i>I didn't wanna do anything,</i>
<i>but he whacked me pretty good.</i>

03:06.120 --> 03:09.033
<i>I may not be the greatest fighter</i>
<i>of all time, but what I learned that day...</i>

03:09.120 --> 03:10.190
Chuck.

03:10.280 --> 03:12.112
<i>...is that I had a gift. I was special.</i>

03:12.960 --> 03:14.360
<i>When you stop any guy in the street</i>

03:14.440 --> 03:17.911
<i>and you ask him</i>
<i>who Chuck Wepner was, he'll tell ya,</i>

03:18.000 --> 03:19.832
<i>"That guy could take a punch."</i>

03:47.160 --> 03:49.834
<i>For a guy who wasn't really a fighter,</i>
<i>I was doing pretty good.</i>

03:50.720 --> 03:53.918
<i>By 1974, I was flying up</i>
<i>the heavyweight ranks</i>

03:54.000 --> 03:56.674
<i>and primed for a shot at the title</i>
<i>against "Big George" Foreman.</i>

03:57.480 --> 04:00.917
<i>The only guy who stood in my way</i>
<i>was Terry Hinke, the Stormin' Mormon.</i>

04:01.000 --> 04:02.559
- Hey, Bleeder!
- What?

04:02.640 --> 04:04.472
Let it go. Let it go. Let it go!

04:04.560 --> 04:06.597
Shit. Bad?

04:06.680 --> 04:08.160
Come on AI, let me see the cut.

04:10.840 --> 04:11.876
Looks pretty bad.

04:11.960 --> 04:13.474
All right, get the fuck out of this corner,

04:13.560 --> 04:15.279
and don't bother me
while I'm working, all right?

04:15.400 --> 04:17.357
<i>Whatever we had to do, we did.</i>

04:17.440 --> 04:21.639
<i>Al and I had an agreement, always</i>
<i>move forward and never stop the fight.</i>

04:21.720 --> 04:23.120
AI, let the doc see the cut.

04:23.240 --> 04:24.913
Sure, have a look there.

04:26.880 --> 04:28.792
- Yeah, he's good. He's good.
- Thanks, Doc.

04:28.880 --> 04:31.031
<i>They called Al "The Butcher,"</i>
<i>but it wasn't just him.</i>

04:31.120 --> 04:32.554
<i>I wouldn't stop, either.</i>

04:32.720 --> 04:35.394
<i>Besides, it wasn't his fault I bled so much.</i>

04:35.480 --> 04:36.960
I cannot close this fuckin' cut.

04:37.040 --> 04:39.350
It's time to send
this fuckin' Mormon back to Utah.

04:39.440 --> 04:40.669
- Are you with me?
- Yeah.

04:40.800 --> 04:41.836
- All right, let's do it.
- Go.

04:41.920 --> 04:44.071
You're on, Chuck. You're on. Hit him.

04:51.800 --> 04:53.712
<i>And the winner by knockout,</i>

04:53.800 --> 04:57.396
<i>in two minutes and 18 seconds</i>
<i>of the 11th round,</i>

04:57.480 --> 05:02.077
<i>and still the North American and</i>
<i>New Jersey heavyweight champion,</i>

05:02.160 --> 05:03.833
<i>Chuck Wepner!</i>

05:08.760 --> 05:09.796
Hey, baby.

05:09.880 --> 05:11.473
Daddy, were you boxing again?

05:11.560 --> 05:13.552
Yeah, as a matter of fact, I was.

05:15.040 --> 05:16.633
