And a little bit of that!

06:02.240 --> 06:05.074
Chuck, no. Come on,
I have to get Kimberly to school.

06:05.160 --> 06:06.992
Plus, I'm still mad at you.

06:07.080 --> 06:09.037
- Will you stop with that, please?
- No!

06:09.120 --> 06:11.760
It's one of Arty's girls. I swear to God,
I never put a hand on her.

06:11.840 --> 06:13.240
It's not your hands I'm worried about.

06:13.320 --> 06:16.358
- I wrote you another poem.
- You can keep your poems.

06:16.480 --> 06:19.075
It's a good one.
Put it on the fridge for you.

06:19.160 --> 06:20.230
Yeah?

06:20.320 --> 06:22.277
- Come on, let me put it in.
- No!

06:22.400 --> 06:24.710
- Just the tip.
- Chuck! No!

06:24.800 --> 06:27.269
- Yeah, come on!
- Chuck, come on! I have 15 minutes...

06:27.360 --> 06:28.555
Fuck!

06:28.640 --> 06:31.872
...to drop her off and get to work!
God. I'm late.

06:38.240 --> 06:39.799
<i>"My One and Only.</i>

06:39.920 --> 06:41.798
<i>"You alone are in my heart</i>

06:41.920 --> 06:44.389
<i>"From break of day till evening start</i>

06:44.480 --> 06:46.312
<i>"All the while I think of you</i>

06:46.400 --> 06:48.960
<i>"And the lucky day that made us two."</i>

06:49.040 --> 06:51.077
<i>I wrote Phyll poems all the time.</i>

06:51.160 --> 06:52.833
<i>Left them around for her, you know?</i>

07:01.760 --> 07:04.594
How you doin'? Chuck Wepner.
Life treating you good?

07:05.680 --> 07:07.034
<i>There was another fighter,</i>

07:07.120 --> 07:08.839
<i>name of Frankie Suppone,</i>
<i>owned the liquor route.</i>

07:08.920 --> 07:12.072
<i>He was retiring, said I had a good</i>
<i>personality and I should take his route.</i>

07:12.200 --> 07:13.600
<i>I'd make a good liquor salesman.</i>

07:13.680 --> 07:15.478
How you doin'? Chuck Wepner.

07:15.560 --> 07:17.552
Let me ask you something, you like Dewar's?

07:17.640 --> 07:18.790
<i>I figured, what the hell?</i>

07:18.880 --> 07:22.396
<i>I may be ranked eighth in the world,</i>
<i>but I still need a freakin' job.</i>

07:23.680 --> 07:25.672
<i>Before that,</i>
<i>I was a bouncer for a couple of years,</i>

07:25.760 --> 07:28.434
<i>then a debt collector for Frank Giglio.</i>

07:28.520 --> 07:31.957
<i>I was never good at roughing guys up.</i>
<i>Too nice.</i>

07:32.040 --> 07:33.952
<i>Felt sorry for them, you know?</i>

07:34.040 --> 07:36.430
<i>Besides, who wants to hang out</i>
<i>with a leg breaker</i>

07:36.560 --> 07:39.837
<i>when you could be rubbing elbows with</i>
<i>the heavyweight champ of New Jersey?</i>

07:41.040 --> 07:43.271
Hey, Champ! Nice fight with Hinke last night.

07:43.400 --> 07:45.631
- Thanks, Joe.
- You really creamed his Mormon ass.

07:45.720 --> 07:47.916
Hey, hey. Bayonne makes,
the world takes, baby.

07:48.000 --> 07:49.150
You got it, brother.

07:50.480 --> 07:52.711
- Hello, hello, hello.
- Hey, here he is!

07:52.800 --> 07:54.678
Congratulations!

07:54.760 --> 07:56.672
